ManSection.Description:
    S is a numerical semigroup and A is a set of integers. Returns a binary relation which is the Hasse diagram of A with  respect to the ordering a\preceq b if b - a in S.

gap> s:=NumericalSemigroup(3,5,7);;
gap> HasseDiagramOfNumericalSemigroup(s,[1,2,3]);
<general mapping: <object> -> <object> >

    S is a numerical semigroup. Applies  with arguments S and its Betti elements.

gap> s:=NumericalSemigroup(3,5,7);;
gap> HasseDiagramOfBettiElementsOfNumericalSemigroup(s);
<general mapping: <object> -> <object> >

    S is a numerical semigroup, n is an integer (optional, if not provided, the multiplicity of the semigroup is taken as its value). Applies  with arguments S and the Apéry set of S with respect to n.

gap> s:=NumericalSemigroup(3,5,7);;
gap> HasseDiagramOfAperyListOfNumericalSemigroup(s);
<general mapping: <object> -> <object> >
gap> HasseDiagramOfAperyListOfNumericalSemigroup(s,10);
<general mapping: <object> -> <object> >

    S is a numerical semigroup and A is a set of integers. Returns the set of antichains (sets of non-comparable elements) of A with respect to the ordering a\preceq b if b - a in S.

gap> s:=NumericalSemigroup(3,5,7);;
gap> AntichainsOfNumericalSemigroup(s,Gaps(s));
[ [  ], [ 4 ], [ 2 ], [ 2, 4 ], [ 1 ], [ 1, 2 ] ]
